# Superpowers (Cursor)

This project vendors [obra/superpowers](https://github.com/obra/superpowers) skills under `.cursor/skills/`.

**User instructions win:** `AGENTS.md`, `docs/current-slice.md`, and explicit user requests override superpowers when they conflict.

## When to load a skill

Before planning features, debugging, finishing work, or requesting review — if a skill might apply (~1% chance), **read it first**:

```text
.cursor/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md
```

Use the **Read** tool on that path (Cursor has no separate Skill tool).

## Thesis-relevant skills

| Situation | Skill |
|-----------|--------|
| New feature / UX change | `brainstorming` → `writing-plans` → `executing-plans` |
| Bug or red screen / Metro | `systematic-debugging` |
| Before saying "done" | `verification-before-completion` |
| Multi-file refactor | `subagent-driven-development` or `dispatching-parallel-agents` |
| Session start / unsure | `using-superpowers` |
| iOS native / CocoaPods | `expo-ios-setup` (project-specific) |

